            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">What vanity surfaces can you respray?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">We respray virtually all bathroom vanity surfaces including laminate, solid timber, MDF, melamine, and previously painted finishes. The key is using the correct bonding primer for each surface type, which ensures the topcoat adheres properly and lasts for years. During the quoting process, we'll identify your surface type and confirm it's suitable.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How long does a vanity respray last?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">A professionally resprayed vanity will typically last 8 to 15 years with normal bathroom use. We use automotive-grade two-part coatings that are highly resistant to moisture, heat, and everyday wear. Proper surface preparation is the biggest factor in longevity &mdash; which is why we never skip the cleaning, sanding, and priming stages.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Will it look like a brand new vanity?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Yes. Because we spray-apply the coating rather than brush or roll it, you get a factory-smooth finish with no brush marks, drips, or uneven texture. Any chips or imperfections are filled and sanded before spraying. The result is indistinguishable from a factory-finished vanity &mdash; most people won't believe it's the same cabinet.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Can you respray the benchtop as well?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">It depends on the material. Laminate benchtops can be resprayed along with the vanity cabinet for a seamless, uniform look. However, stone, engineered stone, and ceramic benchtops are not suitable for respraying. We'll advise you based on photos of your specific vanity during the quoting process.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How long does the respray take to dry?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">The coating is touch-dry within 2 to 4 hours. We recommend waiting 24 hours before placing items back inside the vanity and 48 hours before exposing the surface to water or heavy use. Full cure takes approximately 7 days, during which time you should avoid placing heavy or sharp objects on freshly coated surfaces.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Can I choose any colour for my vanity?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Yes &mdash; we can match any colour you like. Most clients choose modern whites, warm greys, charcoal, or matte black to update the look. We can also colour-match to an existing fixture or paint swatch if you want the vanity to tie in with your bathroom design. Satin and semi-gloss finishes are most popular for vanities.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How do I get a quote for a vanity respray?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Send us 3 to 4 photos of your vanity through our <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/contact/' ) ); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium">contact page</a> and we'll have a fixed-price quote back to you within hours. Include a photo of the front with doors closed, doors open showing the inside, and a close-up of the surface condition. No call-out fee, no obligation. You can also call us directly on <a href="tel:<?php echo timeless_phone_link(); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium"><?php echo timeless_phone(); ?></a>.</p></div></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

